name: Ses01F_script01_3_M029
transcription: Like for instance, there was this one time it had been raining for several days and this kid he just came up to me and he gave me his last pair of dry socks.  He just put them in my pocket.  That's a little thing, you know, but that's what kind of guys I had.

name: Ses01F_script01_3_M030

name: Ses01F_script01_3_M031

name: Ses01F_script01_3_M032

name: Ses01F_script01_3_M033

name: Ses02F_script01_1_M019
transcription: So it's all right then?

name: Ses02F_script01_1_M020
transcription: I'll go ahead with it?

name: Ses02F_script01_1_M021
transcription: Well, then it isn't just my business--

name: Ses02F_script01_1_M022
transcription: Ah, sometimes you infuriate me.  You know that?  I mean, isn't it your business too if I tell Dad and flips--freaks out about it?  I mean, you have such a talent for ignoring things.

name: Ses02F_script01_1_M023
transcription: She's not Larry's girl.

name: Ses02F_script01_1_M024
transcription: I don't know why, but, every time I reach out for something that I want, I have to pull back 'cause someone else will suffer.  My whole bloody life.  Time after time after time.

name: Ses02F_script01_1_M025
transcription: To hell with that.

name: Ses02F_script01_1_M026
transcription: I wanted to get this settled first.

name: Ses02F_script01_1_M027
transcription: Well, if she does, then that's the end of it.  But from her letters, I think she's forgotten him.  I'll find out.  And then we'll thrash it out with Dad, right?  Mom, don't avoid me.

name: Ses02F_script01_1_M028
transcription: So what, I'm not fast with women.

name: Ses02F_script01_1_M029
transcription: Because it is.

name: Ses02F_script01_1_M030
transcription: I can't help it.  I know her best.  I mean, I grew up next door to her.

name: Ses02F_script01_1_M031
transcription: These years when I think of a wife, I think of Annie.  What do you want, a diagram?

name: Ses02F_script01_1_M032
transcription: All right.  All right, then, Mom.

name: Ses02F_script01_1_M033
transcription: I've given it three years of thought.  I thought that if I waited Dad would forget about Larry and we could have a regular wedding and everything happy.

name: Ses02F_script01_1_M034
transcription: But if I can't--if that can't happen here, then I'll have to get out.

name: Ses02F_script01_1_M035
transcription: I'll get out.  I'll get married and go live some place else.  Maybe New York.

name: Ses02F_script01_1_M036
transcription: I've been a good son too long.  A good sucker.  I'm through with it.

name: Ses02F_script01_1_M037
transcription: The business?  The business doesn't inspire me.

name: Ses02F_script01_1_M038
transcription: Yes.  I like it an hour a day.  If I'm gonna grub for my money all day long, at least in the evening I want it beautiful.

name: Ses02F_script01_1_M039
transcription: I want a family.  I want kids.  I want something that I can give myself to.  Annie's in the middle of that.  Now, where do I find it?

name: Ses02F_script01_1_M040
transcription: Yes, on this I would.

name: Ses02F_script01_1_M041
transcription: Then help me stay here.

name: Ses02F_script01_1_M042
transcription: I know.  I know, Mom.  Just help me stay here.

name: Ses02F_script01_1_M043
transcription: I am thinkin' that way.

name: Ses02F_script01_1_M044
transcription: No, you don't.  I'm a pretty tough guy.

name: Ses02F_script01_2_F000
transcription: Why did he invite her here?

name: Ses02F_script01_2_F001
transcription: She's been in New York for three and half years.  Why all of a sudden?

name: Ses02F_script01_2_F002
transcription: Nobody comes seven hundred miles just to see.

name: Ses02F_script01_2_F003
transcription: She's not-

name: Ses02F_script01_2_F004
transcription: -he's not gonna marry her.

name: Ses02F_script01_2_F005
transcription: It's got that all about it.

name: Ses02F_script01_2_F006
transcription: What's going on here, Joe?

name: Ses02F_script01_2_F007
transcription: She's not his girl, Joe.  She knows she's not.

name: Ses02F_script01_2_F008
transcription: Well then why is she still single?  I mean, New York is full of men.  Why isn't she married?  Probably a hundred people told her she's crazy, but she's waited.

name: Ses02F_script01_2_F009
transcription: She knows what I know, that's why.  She's faithful as a rock.  In my worst moments I think of her waiting and I know again that I'm right.

name: Ses02F_script01_2_F010
transcription: Nobody in this house dares take her faith away, Joe?  Strangers might, but not his father, not his brother.

name: Ses02F_script01_2_F011
transcription: I want you to act like he's coming back.  Both of you.  Don't you think I haven't noticed since she got here.  I won't stand for any nonsense.

name: Ses02F_script01_2_F012
transcription: Because if he's not coming back, I'll kill myself.  I mean, laugh--laugh at me, but...

name: Ses02F_script01_2_F013
transcription: But why did that happen the very night she came here?  She sleeps in his room and his memorial breaks to pieces.  Just look.  Look at it.

name: Ses02F_script01_2_F014
transcription: Believe with me, Joe.  I can't stand all alone.

name: Ses02F_script01_2_F015
transcription: Last week, a man turned up in Detroit missing longer than Larry.  I mean, you read it yourself.

name: Ses02F_script01_2_F016
transcription: You, above all, have to believe.

name: Ses02F_script01_2_F017
transcription: Just--just don't stop believing.

name: Ses02F_script01_2_F018
transcription: I can't help it.

name: Ses02F_script01_2_M000
transcription: Why does that bother you?

name: Ses02F_script01_2_M001
transcription: Well, maybe he just wanted to see her again.

name: Ses02F_script01_2_M002
transcription: What do you mean?  He lived next door to the girl all his life.  Why wouldn't he want to see her again?

name: Ses02F_script01_2_M003
transcription: Don't look at me like that.  He didn't tell me anymore than he told you.

name: Ses02F_script01_2_M004
transcription: How do you know he's even thinking of it?

name: Ses02F_script01_2_M005
transcription: Well, so what?

name: Ses02F_script01_2_M006
transcription: Now, listen Kate.

name: Ses02F_script01_2_M007
transcription: You can't read her mind.

name: Ses02F_script01_2_M008
transcription: How do you know why she's waited?

name: Ses02F_script01_2_M009
transcription: Look, it's a nice day.  What are we arguing for?

name: Ses02F_script01_2_M010
transcription: Well, what do you want me to do about it?

name: Ses02F_script01_2_M011
transcription: But Kate--

name: Ses02F_script01_2_M012
transcription: Calm yourself.

name: Ses02F_script01_2_M013
transcription: Calm yourself.

name: Ses02F_script01_2_M014
transcription: All right.  All right.  Calm yourself.

name: Ses02F_script01_2_M015
transcription: What?- Why- Why me above all?

name: Ses02F_script01_2_M016
transcription: What does that mean?  Me above all?

name: Ses02F_script01_2_M017
transcription: Look at you.  Look at you shaking.

name: Ses02F_script01_2_M018
transcription: What have I got to hide?  What the hell is the matter with you Kate?

name: Ses02F_script01_3_F000
transcription: You're the only one I know who loves his parents.

name: Ses02F_script01_3_F001
transcription: It's all right.  It's a good thing.

name: Ses02F_script01_3_F002
transcription: You know, it's lovely here, the air is sweet.

name: Ses02F_script01_3_F003
transcription: No, not sorry.  Um, but, I'm- I'm not gonna stay.

name: Ses02F_script01_3_F004
transcription: Well, for one thing, your mother as much as told me to go.

name: Ses02F_script01_3_F005
transcription: You saw that.  I mean and then, well, you've been kind of, um--

name: Ses02F_script01_3_F006
transcription: Well, kind of embarrassed ever since I got here.

name: Ses02F_script01_3_F007
transcription: I knew they would, your mother anyway.

name: Ses02F_script01_3_F008
transcription: Well,

name: Ses02F_script01_3_F009
transcription: from her point of view, why else would I come?

name: Ses02F_script01_3_F010
transcription: I--I guess this is why I came.

name: Ses02F_script01_3_F011
transcription: Oh, Chris, I've been ready for a long, long time.

name: Ses02F_script01_3_F012
transcription: I almost got married two years ago.

name: Ses02F_script01_3_F013
transcription: You started to write me and--

name: Ses02F_script01_3_F014
transcription: Every day since.

name: Ses02F_script01_3_F015
transcription: Well, I was waiting for you.  I mean, till then you never wrote and when you did, I mean, what did you say?  You can sure be ambiguous sometimes.

name: Ses02F_script01_3_F016
transcription: I will never forgive you.  Why did you wait all these years?  All I did was sit and wonder if I was crazy for thinking of you.

name: Ses02F_script01_3_F017
transcription: Not like that you're not.

name: Ses02F_script01_3_F018
transcription: Like Larry's brother.  Do it like you, Chris.  What is it?

name: Ses02F_script01_3_F019
transcription: No.  What is it, your mother?

name: Ses02F_script01_3_F020
transcription: Then, what's wrong?  I mean, even in your letters there was some--something ashamed.

name: Ses02F_script01_3_F021
transcription: You've gotta tell me.

name: Ses02F_script01_3_F022
transcription: It wouldn't work this way.

name: Ses02F_script01_3_F023
transcription: Yeah, sure.

name: Ses02F_script01_3_F024
transcription: How many?

name: Ses02F_script01_3_F025
transcription: Oh, gee.

name: Ses02F_script01_3_F026
transcription: You still feel that way?

name: Ses02F_script01_3_F027
transcription: 'Cause you mustn't feel that way.  Because you have a right to everything that you have.  Do you understand that?  Everything, Chris, and me too.

name: Ses02F_script01_3_F028
transcription: I mean, and your money, there's nothing wrong with your money.  I mean, your father put hundreds of planes in the air.  A man should be paid for that.

name: Ses02F_script01_3_F029
transcription: What'll I do with a fortune?

name: Ses02F_script01_3_M000
transcription: I know, it went out of style, didn't it?

name: Ses02F_script01_3_M001
transcription: You're not sorry you came?

name: Ses02F_script01_3_M002
transcription: Why?

name: Ses02F_script01_3_M003
transcription: Oh.

name: Ses02F_script01_3_M004
transcription: What?

name: Ses02F_script01_3_M005
transcription: The trouble is, I planned on sort of sneaking up on you over a period of a week or so.  But, they take it for granted that we're all set.

name: Ses02F_script01_3_M006
transcription: Oh.  Would you want to?  I guess you know, this is why I asked you to come.

name: Ses02F_script01_3_M007
transcription: Anne, I love you.  I love you a great deal.  I love you.

name: Ses02F_script01_3_M008
transcription: I have no imagination.  That's all I know to tell you.

name: Ses02F_script01_3_M009
transcription: I'm embarrassing you and I didn't want to tell it to you here.  I wanted some place we'd never been before.  A place where we'd be brand new to each other.

name: Ses02F_script01_3_M010
transcription: You feel it's wrong here, don't you?  This yard, this chair.  I want you to be ready for me.  I don't want to have to win you away from anything.

name: Ses02F_script01_3_M011
transcription: And he's gone forever.  You're sure?

name: Ses02F_script01_3_M012
transcription: Why didn't you?

name: Ses02F_script01_3_M013
transcription: You felt something that far back?

name: Ses02F_script01_3_M014
transcription: Anne, why didn't you let me know?

name: Ses02F_script01_3_M015
transcription: Give me a kiss, Anne.  Give me a-

name: Ses02F_script01_3_M016
transcription: oh God, I kissed you.  I kissed Annie.  How long--how long I've been waiting to kiss you.

name: Ses02F_script01_3_M017
transcription: Oh, Annie, we're gonna live now.  I'm gonna make you so happy.

name: Ses02F_script01_3_M018
transcription: I kissed you.

name: Ses02F_script01_3_M019
transcription: Let's drive someplace.  I want to be alone with you.

name: Ses02F_script01_3_M020
transcription: No.  Nothing like that.

name: Ses02F_script01_3_M021
transcription: Yeah, I suppose I have been.  But it's going from me.

name: Ses02F_script01_3_M022
transcription: I don't know how to start.

name: Ses02F_script01_3_M023
transcription: It's all mixed up with so many other things.  You remember overseas, I was in command of a company?

name: Ses02F_script01_3_M024
transcription: Well, I lost them.

name: Ses02F_script01_3_M025
transcription: Just about all.

name: Ses02F_script01_3_M026
transcription: It takes some time for a guy to toss that off.  'Cause they weren't just men.

name: Ses02F_script01_3_M027
transcription: For instance, one time, it had been raining several days and this kid came to me and gave me his last pair of dry socks.  I put them in pocket.  It's only a little thing, but that's the kind of guys I had.

name: Ses02F_script01_3_M028
transcription: They didn't die, they killed themselves for each other.  I mean that exactly.  A little more selfish and they'd have been here today.

name: Ses02F_script01_3_M029
transcription: I got this idea watching them go down.  Everything was being destroyed, see, but it seemed that there was one new thing being made.  A sort of responsibility.  Man for man.

name: Ses02F_script01_3_M030
transcription: You know what I mean?  To show that, to bring that onto the Earth again, like some kind of monument and everyone would feel it standing behind him and it would make a difference to him.

name: Ses02F_script01_3_M031
transcription: Then I came back and it was incredible.  There was no meaning in it here.  The whole thing to them seemed like sort of a bus accident.  I went to work with Dad and that rat race again.

name: Ses02F_script01_3_M032
transcription: And I felt what you said, ashamed somehow 'cause nobody was changed at all.  It seemed to make suckers out of a lot of guys.  I felt wrong to be alive to open the new bank book, drive the new car, see the new refrigerator.

name: Ses02F_script01_3_M033
transcription: I mean, you can take those things out of a war, but when you drive that car, you've gotta know that it came out of the love a man can have for a man.  You've gotta be a little better because of it.

name: Ses02F_script01_3_M034
transcription: Because otherwise all you have is really loot and there's blood on it.  And I didn't want to take any of it.  And I guess that included you.

name: Ses02F_script01_3_M035
transcription: I want you now Annie.

name: Ses02F_script01_3_M036
transcription: I know Annie.  Annie, I'm gonna make a fortune for you.

name: Ses02F_script02_1_F000
transcription: Fine.

name: Ses02F_script02_1_F001
transcription: What flashlight?

name: Ses02F_script02_1_F002
transcription: That's not your flashlight.

name: Ses02F_script02_1_F003
transcription: It's ours.  It's mine too.

name: Ses02F_script02_1_F004
transcription: You kept saying my flashlight, if as if somehow it's just yours.  I mean is that supposed to make me feel?

name: Ses02F_script02_1_F005
transcription: Yeah.

name: Ses02F_script02_1_F006
transcription: I'm cold.

name: Ses02F_script02_1_F007
transcription: It's after eleven, let's just go home.

name: Ses02F_script02_1_F008
transcription: There is no point in coming down here.

name: Ses02F_script02_1_F009
transcription: That's my point.

name: Ses02F_script02_1_F010
transcription: So, let's go.

name: Ses02F_script02_1_F011
transcription: Not particularly.

name: Ses02F_script02_1_F012
transcription: I just don't.  It's stupid.

name: Ses02F_script02_1_F013
transcription: Pass up what?  These little fish swim onto the beach, they flop around, and swim away.  And then they die.

name: Ses02F_script02_1_F014
transcription: What are you so excited about?  I mean, it's not a moon landing we're talking about here.  It's fish.  It's a fish nobody even eats.

name: Ses02F_script02_1_F015
transcription: Ah, Augie.

name: Ses02F_script02_1_F016
transcription: I'm just not.

name: Ses02F_script02_1_F017
transcription: Yeah.

name: Ses02F_script02_1_F018
transcription: Last year, you will also remember our shoes got wet, I got sand in my panties, you got a sore throat, we got in a big fight over nothing, and we didn't see the grunions.

name: Ses02F_script02_1_F019
transcription: We didn't see them the first time either.

name: Ses02F_script02_1_F020
transcription: That's the wind.

name: Ses02F_script02_1_F021
transcription: About what?

name: Ses02F_script02_1_F022
transcription: It's ridiculous.

name: Ses02F_script02_1_M000
transcription: What time is it?  They're supposed to run around midnight.

name: Ses02F_script02_1_M001
transcription: This is great, isn't it?  Look at the night we've got here, couldn't be better.

name: Ses02F_script02_1_M002
transcription: I would have liked to have gone a little further up the coast to get away from the lights and the people, but I was afraid we'd miss it.

name: Ses02F_script02_1_M003
transcription: How you doing?

name: Ses02F_script02_1_M004
transcription: Is that--no--is that just foam?  I can't even tell.

name: Ses02F_script02_1_M005
transcription: Well, I guess we can tell, it probably isn't right?  Probably be unmistakable don't you think?

name: Ses02F_script02_1_M006
transcription: How you doing?  Aw, you know what I forgot?  I forgot to bring my flashlight.  Oh, how could I be so stupid?  I should've brought my flashlight.

name: Ses02F_script02_1_M007
transcription: You know, the flashlight, the silver one.  There's only one isn't there?

name: Ses02F_script02_1_M008
transcription: Who's is it?

name: Ses02F_script02_1_M009
transcription: Oh, well sure.

name: Ses02F_script02_1_M010
transcription: Right, of course.  Our flashlight.  Mine and yours.  I mean, me flashlight is su flashlight naturally.

name: Ses02F_script02_1_M011
transcription: How could we forget to bring it?  I hope the moon stays out.

name: Ses02F_script02_1_M012
transcription: I wonder, do they always run during a full moon?  I can't remember if it was full last year.  Do you remember?

name: Ses02F_script02_1_M013
transcription: You cold?  Do you want my jacket?  Oh, we should've brought the blanket.  Our blanket.

name: Ses02F_script02_1_M014
transcription: This is great, isn't it?  A six pack would be just the ticket right now.

name: Ses02F_script02_1_M015
transcription: I can't believe I forgot.  I'm like a kid.  It's amazing I got out of the house with my fly zipped.

name: Ses02F_script02_1_M016
transcription: You think they can hear us talk?  Or feel the vibrations in the sand when we move around?

name: Ses02F_script02_1_M017
transcription: Do you want my jacket?

name: Ses02F_script02_1_M018
transcription: Are you kidding?  We'd miss it.  We just got here.  What's the point of coming down here if we just turn around and go home.

name: Ses02F_script02_1_M019
transcription: Right.

name: Ses02F_script02_1_M020
transcription: That's my point too.

name: Ses02F_script02_1_M021
transcription: No. No. That's not my point.  The point is there's no point in coming down if we just leave.  Don't you want to see it?

name: Ses02F_script02_1_M022
transcription: Why not?

name: Ses02F_script02_1_M023
transcription: Honey, this is a natural phenomenon.  I mean this only happens once a year, you know.

name: Ses02F_script02_1_M024
transcription: Think about the people in Kansas, they had to get plane tickets and hotel reservations to see this.  We live forty minutes away.  It's too good to pass up.

name: Ses02F_script02_1_M025
transcription: Yeah, but that moment on the beach, is the highlight of their little lives.  All that flopping is laying eggs or what do you--spawning or mating.  I mean,

name: Ses02F_script02_1_M026
transcription: this is a big night for these guys.  Life's last orgy.

name: Ses02F_script02_1_M027
transcription: Yeah they do.

name: Ses02F_script02_1_M028
transcription: Alright.  But it's fish that do something that none of the other fish do.  Like the swallows returning to Capistrano or the lemmings throwing themselves off the cliffs.

name: Ses02F_script02_1_M029
transcription: There's--there's a bit of the magic--some unexplainable here.  I don't see how you can not be interested.

name: Ses02F_script02_1_M030
transcription: For real?

name: Ses02F_script02_1_M031
transcription: I don't get it.  The first time we came here, you said it was the best night of your life.

name: Ses02F_script02_1_M032
transcription: And last year, I remember specifically you were so excited to go that you stubbed your toe rushing me out of the house and didn't even notice until we got in the car.

name: Ses02F_script02_1_M033
transcription: We weren't in a good spot.

name: Ses02F_script02_1_M034
transcription: We just weren't in a good spot.  This is a much better spot.  Believe me, I've got good instincts for these things.

name: Ses02F_script02_1_M035
transcription: There is that--no that's just seaweed isn't it?

name: Ses02F_script02_1_M036
transcription: Oh man, this is great, isn't it?  I wouldn't miss this for anything.  Here, think about this, all right, I know you're not interested, but think about this.

name: Ses02F_script02_1_M037
transcription: Somewhere out there, this huge mass of silver fish swimming this way.

name: Ses02F_script02_1_M038
transcription: They don't know why, we don't know why.  Nobody sent them an invitation or a map, it wasn't a decision, just-

name: Ses02F_script02_1_M039
transcription: all as one, this time release instinctual little firecracker went off and they all turned and formed a line as long as the California coast and started swimming.  And they're swimming right now as if that's all that matters.

name: Ses02F_script02_1_M040
transcription: It's like single mindedness with no mind.  It's urgency that's pure urge.  They don't know what drives them.  They don't ask it a question or give it a name.

name: Ses02F_script02_1_M041
transcription: They just turn as one and start the swim that brings them right here to where we stand, for a massive celebration of sex and death.

name: Ses02F_script02_1_M042
transcription: Ah, God, I'm giving myself goose bumps.  Look, all my hairs are popped up.

name: Ses02F_script02_1_M043
transcription: Well, so what do you think?

name: Ses02F_script02_1_M044
transcription: What I was saying.

name: Ses02F_script02_2_F000
transcription: About what?

name: Ses02F_script02_2_F001
transcription: It's ridiculous.

name: Ses02F_script02_2_F002
transcription: It's PR.  Somebody sold you a bill of goods that this wonderful event is gonna take place on the beach.

name: Ses02F_script02_2_F003
transcription: Sure, everybody's told the same story.  It keeps us all excited.  It keeps us coming back for more.  It keeps us thinking that life is gonna start any second now if we could just find the right spot and get in on the action.

name: Ses02F_script02_2_F004
transcription: Well, I'm sorry, but it's still just fish to me.

name: Ses02F_script02_2_F005
transcription: God damn it, Augie, don't ask me that.  I hate it when you ask me that.  You always ask me that.  It's insulting.

name: Ses02F_script02_2_F006
transcription: We just have different ideas of what this evening is supposed to look like.

name: Ses02F_script02_2_F007
transcription: For heaven sake, we're not going to see the grunions.

name: Ses02F_script02_2_F008
transcription: We never do, do we?  I mean, have we ever?

name: Ses02F_script02_2_F009
transcription: Twice is every time we've tried. That's ever.

name: Ses02F_script02_2_F010
transcription: No, we won't.  It's pointless.  It's like waiting up to see Santa Claus.

name: Ses02F_script02_2_F011
transcription: I mean, I feel like my whole life is gonna be spent standing on the beach with my eyes wide open and my hands clasped expectantly waiting for the fish to show up.  And the fish won't show up.

name: Ses02F_script02_2_F012

transcription: Do you remember the first time we came to see it?  It was about four years ago, right after we got married.

name: Ses02F_script02_2_F016

name: Ses02F_script02_2_F018

name: Ses02F_script02_2_F019

name: Ses02F_script02_2_F020
transcription: I'd rather not remember some things.  I would rather not hope for some things.

transcription: No.

transcription: No.

transcription: I mean, this is just this.  It includes a lot and everything, but it isn't something else.  Do you have any idea what I'm trying to say?

name: Ses02F_script02_2_F036
transcription: Oh, for heaven sake, whatever I'm doing, I'd rather be doing it with you.

transcription: Oh, don't be ridiculous.  I mean, don't you know that?

name: Ses02F_script02_2_F038
transcription: You're the one who probably wishes you were with someone else.  Someone who--you'd rather enjoy yourself and didn't take everything so hard.

name: Ses02F_script02_2_F039
transcription: Okay.  Fine so.  We're in the wrong spot, but we're with the right person.

name: Ses02F_script02_2_F040

name: Ses02F_script02_2_F041

name: Ses02F_script02_2_M019
transcription: It was in the car, right?  Driving past the Knickerbocker Liquor Locker, you said, "let's get some champagne," and I said, "time's a wasting" or something like that, right?

name: Ses02F_script02_2_M020

name: Ses02F_script02_2_M021

name: Ses02F_script02_2_M022

transcription: Right.

name: Ses02F_script02_2_M035

name: Ses02F_script02_2_M036

name: Ses02F_script02_2_M039
transcription: Yeah?

transcription: I don't know.  It seemed like a pretty good spot to me.  I mean, look at the view you have of the moon from here.

name: Ses02F_script02_2_M042
transcription: Well, look what we have here.

name: Ses02F_script02_2_M043
transcription: It's not champagne.

name: Ses02F_script02_2_M044
transcription: You still cold?  Do you wanna go home?

transcription: Shh.  If we're very quiet the fish might come.

name: Ses02F_script03_1_F000
transcription: Do you think it's them?

name: Ses02F_script03_1_F002
transcription: What're we gonna do?

transcription: Now and always, sweet.

name: Ses02F_script03_1_F004
transcription: It was bound to come sooner or later.

name: Ses02F_script03_1_F005
transcription: Ah, it send shivers up my spine.

name: Ses02F_script03_1_F006
transcription: Behave exquisitely.

name: Ses02F_script03_1_F007
transcription: Oh, of course.  I shall probably do a court curtsy.

transcription: What's so horrible is that one can't stay happy.

name: Ses02F_script03_1_F009
transcription: It's true.  The whole business is a very poor joke.

name: Ses02F_script03_1_F010
transcription: Yes, meaning just that.

transcription: Don't laugh at me.  I'm serious.

name: Ses02F_script03_1_F012

transcription: Let's be superficial and pity the poor philosophers.  Let's blow our trumpets and squeakers and enjoy the party as much as we can.  Like quite idiotic, very small school children.  Let's savor the delight of the moment.

transcription: Come and kiss me, darling, before your body rots and worms pop in and out of your eye sockets.

transcription: I don't care what you do.  See, you could paint yourself green and dance naked in the Place Vendome and rush off madly with all the men in the world and I shan't say a word.  As long as you love me best.

name: Ses02F_script03_1_M029
transcription: The worst one was in Cannes when your curling iron burnt a hole in my new dressing gown.

name: Ses02F_script03_1_M030

name: Ses02F_script03_1_M031
transcription: I didn't hit you very hard.

name: Ses02F_script03_2_F012
transcription: Well, it's become a habit with you.

name: Ses02F_script03_2_F013
transcription: Don't be so stupid.

name: Ses02F_script03_2_F014
transcription: What?

name: Ses02F_script03_2_F015
transcription: No, just making myself fascinating for you.

name: Ses02F_script03_2_F016
transcription: A woman's job is to allure the man.  Watch me a minute, will you?

name: Ses02F_script03_2_F017
transcription: No, it isn't.

name: Ses02F_script03_2_F018
transcription: Oh, be quiet.

name: Ses02F_script03_2_F019
transcription: Doesn't seem to have worked such wonders with you.

name: Ses02F_script03_2_F020
transcription: Adders don't snap, they sting.

name: Ses02F_script03_2_F021

transcription: Shut up.

name: Ses02F_script03_2_F040

name: Ses02F_script03_2_F041

name: Ses02F_script03_2_F043
transcription: Thank God I realized what you are-- I'd never marry you again ever in my life. You're a cruel fiend and I hate you. You're a beast. You're a beast--I hate you. Stop it.  Stop it.

name: Ses02F_script03_2_M001
transcription: I knew nothing of the sort.  You took presents from him.

name: Ses02F_script03_2_M003
transcription: You went out of your way to torture me over Peter Burden.

name: Ses02F_script03_2_M027

name: Ses02F_script03_2_M028

name: Ses02F_script03_2_M030

name: Ses02F_script03_2_M031

name: Ses02F_script03_2_M032

name: Ses02F_script03_2_M035

transcription: Well, it is. I mean, what do you want me to do? You're grown up; you know what's going on in your mind.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_F023
transcription: Well, you better make sure your father's not- No- I'm just saying.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_F024
transcription: Yeah, well I ignore what I got to ignore.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_F025
transcription: And she-she's Larry's girl.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_F026
transcription: Well, from your father's point of view she is. I mean, he's still alive. You've got no right to take her.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_F027
transcription: If you go on from that point, I don't know where you go.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_F028
transcription: 'Cause listen, I'm telling you, I don't know where to go from there. Do you?

name: Ses03F_script01_1_F029
transcription: What do you want from me?

name: Ses03F_script01_1_F030
transcription: You're a considerate fella and there's nothing wrong in that.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_F031
transcription: There's nothing wrong with it.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_F032
transcription: You didn't ask her yet?

name: Ses03F_script01_1_F033
transcription: Well, how do you know she's going to marry you? I mean, what if she feels the same way as your father?

name: Ses03F_script01_1_F034
transcription: You know, the trouble is you've never had enough women. No, you never did.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_F035
transcription: I don't understand why it has to be her.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_F036
transcription: That's a good answer, but it doesn't answer anything.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_F037
transcription: I mean, you haven't seen her since the war. I mean, it's been five years.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_F038
transcription: No, I don't want a diagram.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_F039
transcription: He thinks he's coming back. You go-go on and marry her, I mean, you're pronouncing her dead. And what's going to happen to your father, huh? I don't know. Do you?

name: Ses03F_script01_1_F040
transcription: Just, listen. Give it more thought, is all.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_F041
transcription: What the hell is this?

name: Ses03F_script01_1_F042
transcription: You're crazy.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_F043
transcription: You're what-you're going to leave the business? But you can't do that. What the hell is this?

name: Ses03F_script01_1_F044
transcription: Oh, you have to be inspired.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_F045
transcription: Tell me something.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_F046
transcription: You'd leave that business.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_F047
transcription: You can't do that.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_F048
transcription: All right, but you can't do that. You can't talk like that.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_F049
transcription: We've worked all our lives for you. Only for you, Chris. The whole shootin' match is for you.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_F050
transcription: I'm going to.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_F051
transcription: You just can't talk like that.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_F052
transcription: I don't know you, do I?

name: Ses03F_script01_1_F053
transcription: Yeah. I can see that.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_M000
transcription: He saw it.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_M001
transcription: He was out there when it happened.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_M002
transcription: Um, about four this morning. Uh- I heard a crack and I looked out and I saw him standing there.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_M003
transcription: I don't know. But after it cracked he went back in the house and he cried in the kitchen.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_M004
transcription: No, I uh-, I figured the best thing to do was to leave him alone.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_M005
transcription: I could hear it right through the floor.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_M006
transcription: I guess he is.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_M007
transcription: I don't know.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_M008
transcription: But I know one thing, mom. We've made a terrible mistake with dad.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_M009
transcription: Being dishonest with him. That kind of thing always pays off and now it's paying off.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_M010
transcription: You know Larry's not coming back and I know that too. Why do we go on letting him think that we believe with him?

name: Ses03F_script01_1_M011
transcription: No, I don't want to argue with him, but it's time that he realized that no one believes that Larry's coming back anymore.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_M012
transcription: We got to tell him that.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_M013
transcription: You know, for God's sakes it's been three years. No one comes back after three years. It's insane.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_M014
transcription: All right. Just- Sit down, mom. I want to talk to you.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_M015
transcription: All right. All right. Just come on, sit down.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_M016
transcription: You know-you know why I asked Annie here, right?

name: Ses03F_script01_1_M017
transcription: You know.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_M018
transcription: I want to ask her to marry me.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_M019
transcription: Come on, you know that's not only my business.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_M020
transcription: So it's all right. I'll just go ahead with it.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_M021
transcription: See, then it's not just my business. God, you have

name: Ses03F_script01_1_M022
transcription: -Oh, you infuriate me sometimes. You know, it's not just my business too if dad throws a fit.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_M023
transcription: God. You have such a talent for ignoring things.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_M024
transcription: No, she is not Larry's girl.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_M025
transcription: Oh, I don't know.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_M026
transcription: Every time I reach out for something I have to pull back because other people will suffer. My whole entire life, time and time after time.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_M027
transcription: To hell with that.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_M028
transcription: I didn't ask Annie yet.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_M029
transcription: I wanted to get this settled first.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_M030
transcription: Well then I guess it's over then. But from her letters I think she's forgotten him.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_M031
transcription: I'll find out. But then after it's all over we'll thrash it out with dad, right?

name: Ses03F_script01_1_M032
transcription: Mom, don't avoid me.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_M033
transcription: So what? I'm not fast with women.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_M034
transcription: Because it is.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_M035
transcription: I just-

name: Ses03F_script01_1_M036
transcription: It just is. I-

name: Ses03F_script01_1_M037
transcription: I grew up with her. Okay. All these years, when I think of someone I want to be my wife I think of Annie. What do you want, a diagram?

name: Ses03F_script01_1_M038
transcription: Okay. All right, then.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_M039
transcription: No, I've given it three years of thought.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_M040
transcription: And I thought that if I waited then dad would forget about Larry and then we could have a regular wedding and everything happy.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_M041
transcription: But if I can't have that here then I'll get out.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_M042
transcription: I'll get out. I'll marry her somewhere else. Maybe New York.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_M043
transcription: I've been a sucker too long. I'm through with it.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_M044
transcription: The business. The business doesn't inspire me.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_M045
transcription: Yes. I like it an hour out of the day. If I have to grub for money all day long at least that evening I want it beautiful. I want a wife. I want a family. I want some kids. I want to build something I can give myself to.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_M046
transcription: Now, Annie's in the middle of all that.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_M047
transcription: Now, where do I find it?

name: Ses03F_script01_1_M048
transcription: Yes. On this I would.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_M049
transcription: Then help me stay here.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_M050
transcription: Okay. Just-

name: Ses03F_script01_1_M051
transcription: Yeah, I know, I know, just help me stay here, all right?

name: Ses03F_script01_1_M052
transcription: I am thinking like that.

name: Ses03F_script01_1_M053
transcription: No, you don't. I'm a pretty tough guy.

name: Ses03F_script01_2_F000
transcription: Why did you invite her here?

name: Ses03F_script01_2_F001
transcription: She's been in New York for three-and-a-half years. She don't just suddenly come and-

name: Ses03F_script01_2_F002
transcription: You don't travel seven hundred miles just to see.

name: Ses03F_script01_2_F003
transcription: He's not going to marry her.

name: Ses03F_script01_2_F004
transcription: It's got that about it.

name: Ses03F_script01_2_F005
transcription: What's going on here, Joe?

name: Ses03F_script01_2_F006
transcription: She's not Larry's girl. She knows that.

name: Ses03F_script01_2_F007
transcription: Then why is she married? Then why isn't she married? She's been in New York and there's hundreds of single men there.

name: Ses03F_script01_2_F008
transcription: I'm sure hundreds of them asked her and told her that she's foolish, but no.

name: Ses03F_script01_2_F009
transcription: She's waited.

name: Ses03F_script01_2_F010
transcription: Because she thinks like me, that's why.

name: Ses03F_script01_2_F011
transcription: She's faithful as a rock, don't you know. In my worst moments I can think of her-

name: Ses03F_script01_2_F012
transcription: I think again, that I'm-I'm right.

name: Ses03F_script01_2_F013
transcription: Nobody in my house better ever dare-dare to challenge her faith. Maybe strangers, but not his father, not his brother.

name: Ses03F_script01_2_F014
transcription: Because he's not coming back. Then what do I got to live for? I'll kill myself.

name: Ses03F_script01_2_F015
transcription: Don't, don't laugh at me, don't laugh at me.

name: Ses03F_script01_2_F016
transcription: Look at it. Because why, when she came here and she slept in his room, the memorial broke into pieces. Look at it, look at it, Joe.

name: Ses03F_script01_2_F017
transcription: You got to believe, believe with me because I can't stand all alone.

name: Ses03F_script01_2_F018
transcription: No, you've got to believe.

name: Ses03F_script01_2_F019
transcription: Believe, Joe. You above all people have got to believe.

name: Ses03F_script01_2_F020
transcription: You got to keep believing.

name: Ses03F_script01_2_F021
transcription: I can't help it.

name: Ses03F_script01_2_M000
transcription: Why? Does that bother you?

name: Ses03F_script01_2_M001
transcription: Well, maybe, maybe he just wanted to see her.

name: Ses03F_script01_2_M002
transcription: What do you mean? They lived next door to each other their entire lives. Why shouldn't he want to see her? Hey, don't look at me like that. I don't know anymore than you do.

name: Ses03F_script01_2_M003
transcription: How do you know he's even thinking about it?

name: Ses03F_script01_2_M004
transcription: Well, so what?

name: Ses03F_script01_2_M005
transcription: Listen, kid-

name: Ses03F_script01_2_M006
transcription: You can't read her mind.

name: Ses03F_script01_2_M007
transcription: How do you know why she's waited?

name: Ses03F_script01_2_M008
transcription: Look, it's a nice day. What are we arguing for?

name: Ses03F_script01_2_M009
transcription: Calm yourself.

name: Ses03F_script01_2_M010
transcription: Calm yourself.

name: Ses03F_script01_2_M011
transcription: All right. All right. Calm yourself.

name: Ses03F_script01_2_M012
transcription: Okay. Just calm yourself.

name: Ses03F_script01_2_M013
transcription: Why me, above all?

name: Ses03F_script01_2_M014
transcription: Huh?

name: Ses03F_script01_2_M015
transcription: Why me above all?

name: Ses03F_script01_2_M016
transcription: Look at you, you're shaking.

name: Ses03F_script01_2_M017
transcription: What have I got to hide?

name: Ses03F_script01_2_M018
transcription: Huh? What the hell's the matter with you, Kate?

name: Ses03F_script01_3_F000
transcription: You're the only one I know that still loves his parents.

name: Ses03F_script01_3_F001
transcription: No, it's all right. There's nothing wrong in that, you know.

name: Ses03F_script01_3_F002
transcription: It's really lovely here. The air is sweet.

name: Ses03F_script01_3_F003
transcription: No. I'm not sorry. It's-

name: Ses03F_script01_3_F004
transcription: I can't stay.

name: Ses03F_script01_3_F005
transcription: Well, for one thing, your mother so much has told me to go. [LAUGHTER].

name: Ses03F_script01_3_F006
transcription: Look,

name: Ses03F_script01_3_F007
transcription: you've been acting kind of, well, you know.

name: Ses03F_script01_3_F008
transcription: Well, you've been embarrassed ever since I came.

name: Ses03F_script01_3_F009
transcription: Yeah.

name: Ses03F_script01_3_F010
transcription: Yeah, they would. Especially your mom.

name: Ses03F_script01_3_F011
transcription: Well, I mean,

name: Ses03F_script01_3_F012
transcription: from her opinion, why else would I come here?

name: Ses03F_script01_3_F013
transcription: Well, I guess that's why I came.

name: Ses03F_script01_3_F014
transcription: I've been ready for a long, long time.

name: Ses03F_script01_3_F015
transcription: Look

name: Ses03F_script01_3_F016
transcription: I was almost married two years ago.

name: Ses03F_script01_3_F017
transcription: 'Cause you started to write me.

name: Ses03F_script01_3_F018
transcription: Every day since.

name: Ses03F_script01_3_F019
transcription: Well, I don't know, you didn't write until then and then when you did, what'd you say?

name: Ses03F_script01_3_F020
transcription: You always can be so ambiguous.

name: Ses03F_script01_3_F021
transcription: I don't know if I ever can forgive you for that. Why'd you wait so long? I sat in my room wondering if I was crazy for thinking about you.

name: Ses03F_script01_3_F022
transcription: Not like that, you're not.

name: Ses03F_script01_3_F023
transcription: Like Larry's brother. Do it like you, Chris.

name: Ses03F_script01_3_F024
transcription: What is it?

name: Ses03F_script01_3_F025
transcription: No. What is it? Is it your mother?

name: Ses03F_script01_3_F026
transcription: Well then tell me what's wrong. I mean, even in your letters there's something ashamed.

name: Ses03F_script01_3_F027
transcription: You should tell me.

name: Ses03F_script01_3_F028
transcription: But, Chris, it wouldn't work like this.

name: Ses03F_script01_3_F029
transcription: Yeah, sure.

name: Ses03F_script01_3_F030
transcription: How many?

name: Ses03F_script01_3_F031
transcription: Geez.

name: Ses03F_script01_3_F032
transcription: And you still feel that way?

name: Ses03F_script01_3_F033
transcription: Because you can't feel that way, never again, Chris. You hear me? Never. I mean, the money and me too.

name: Ses03F_script01_3_F034
transcription: I mean, there's nothing wrong in that money, and your father put good planes up in the air and you should be proud of that. A man should be paid for that.

name: Ses03F_script01_3_F035
transcription: What am I going to do with a fortune?

name: Ses03F_script01_3_M000
transcription: Yeah. I know. It went out of style, didn't it?

name: Ses03F_script01_3_M001
transcription: You're not sorry you came?

name: Ses03F_script01_3_M002
transcription: Why not?

name: Ses03F_script01_3_M003
transcription: Well-

name: Ses03F_script01_3_M004
transcription: What?

name: Ses03F_script01_3_M005
transcription: Yes, I guess I have been. But it's going from me now.

name: Ses03F_script01_3_M006
transcription: Oh look, um, well, the thing is, I was planning on, planning on sort of sneaking up on you over a week or so, and they-they take it for granted we're all set.

name: Ses03F_script01_3_M007
transcription: How did you know?

name: Ses03F_script01_3_M008
transcription: Well, uh- would you want to?

name: Ses03F_script01_3_M009
transcription: I, I guess that's why I asked you to come.

name: Ses03F_script01_3_M010
transcription: Oh, Annie.

name: Ses03F_script01_3_M011
transcription: Annie, I love you.

name: Ses03F_script01_3_M012
transcription: I love you a great deal.

name: Ses03F_script01_3_M013
transcription: I-I love you. I have no imagination. That's all I know how to tell it.

name: Ses03F_script01_3_M014
transcription: I'm embarrassing you. I didn't want to tell you it here. I wanted to go somewhere that would be brand-new to each other. It feels wrong here, don't you? This yard and this chair.

name: Ses03F_script01_3_M015
transcription: I don't want to win you from anybody. I want you to be ready for me.

name: Ses03F_script01_3_M016
transcription: Then he's gone forever. You're sure?

name: Ses03F_script01_3_M017
transcription: Why didn't you?

name: Ses03F_script01_3_M018
transcription: You felt something that far back?

name: Ses03F_script01_3_M019
transcription: Why didn't you let me know?

name: Ses03F_script01_3_M020
transcription: Give me a kiss, Annie.

name: Ses03F_script01_3_M021
transcription: Give me-

name: Ses03F_script01_3_M022
transcription: [LAUGHTER]. God, I kissed Annie. I kissed Annie. How long, how long I've been waiting to kiss you.

name: Ses03F_script01_3_M023
transcription: We're going to live now. I'm going to make you so happy.

name: Ses03F_script01_3_M024
transcription: I kissed you.

name: Ses03F_script01_3_M025
transcription: Let's drive somewhere. I want to be alone with you.

name: Ses03F_script01_3_M026
transcription: No, no, no, no. Nothing like that.

name: Ses03F_script01_3_M027
transcription: Yeah. I guess there is. I guess I was, but uh- it's going from me now.

name: Ses03F_script01_3_M028
transcription: I don't know where to start.

name: Ses03F_script01_3_M029
transcription: You know when I went overseas. I said I was in command of a company.

name: Ses03F_script01_3_M030
transcription: Well, I lost them.

name: Ses03F_script01_3_M031
transcription: Just about all.

name: Ses03F_script01_3_M032
transcription: It takes a little while to toss that off. Because they weren't just men.

name: Ses03F_script01_3_M033
transcription: For instance, one time, it had to have been raining several days. There was this one kid, he came up to me and he gave me his last pair of dry socks. Put them in my pocket.

name: Ses03F_script01_3_M034
transcription: I mean, that's-that's only a little thing, but that's the kind of guys I had. They didn't just die. They killed themselves for each other. And I mean that exactly. A little more selfish and they'd still be here today.

name: Ses03F_script01_3_M035
transcription: And I, and I thought something watching them go down.

name: Ses03F_script01_3_M036
transcription: Everything was being destroyed, see, but there was one new thing that was being created. A kind of responsibility, man for man. You understand me?

name: Ses03F_script01_3_M037
transcription: And to show that-to bring that onto the earth like some sort of monument standing right behind us where everyone could feel it and it would make a difference to him.

name: Ses03F_script01_3_M038
transcription: And I came back here and it was incredible. There was no meaning in that here. The whole thing to them was a bus accident.

name: Ses03F_script01_3_M039
transcription: And I went to work with dad and that rat race again. And I felt what you said-ashamed somehow. Because nobody was changed at all. It seemed to make a sucker out of a lot of guys.

name: Ses03F_script01_3_M040
transcription: And I felt wrong to be alive. To drive the car, to see the new checkbook, to see the new refrigerator. I mean, you can take those things out of the war. But you got to know that when you drive that car that that came out of the love a man can have for another man. And you got to be a little bit better because of that.

name: Ses03F_script01_3_M041
transcription: Otherwise, what you have here is loot; and there's blood on it.

name: Ses03F_script01_3_M042
transcription: And I didn't want to take any of it.

name: Ses03F_script01_3_M043
transcription: And I guess that included you.

name: Ses03F_script01_3_M044
transcription: I want you now, Annie.

name: Ses03F_script01_3_M045
transcription: Annie,

name: Ses03F_script01_3_M046
transcription: Annie, I'm going to make a fortune for you.

name: Ses03F_script02_1_F000
transcription: Fine.

name: Ses03F_script02_1_F001
transcription: What flashlight?

name: Ses03F_script02_1_F002
transcription: That's not your flashlight; it's ours. It's mine too.

name: Ses03F_script02_1_F003
transcription: I don't understand why you're always saying oh, it's mine, it's mine. It's not like it's just your flashlight. I mean, how do you think that makes me feel?

name: Ses03F_script02_1_F004
transcription: Yes.

name: Ses03F_script02_1_F005
transcription: I'm cold.

name: Ses03F_script02_1_F006
transcription: It's past eleven, let's go home.

name: Ses03F_script02_1_F007
transcription: There is no point in coming down here.

name: Ses03F_script02_1_F008
transcription: That's my point.

name: Ses03F_script02_1_F009
transcription: Well, so let's go.

name: Ses03F_script02_1_F010
transcription: Not particularly.

name: Ses03F_script02_1_F011
transcription: I don't know. I just don't.

name: Ses03F_script02_1_F012
transcription: Pass up what? A bunch of fish. They swim up to the beach and they flop around and they swim away and then they die.

name: Ses03F_script02_1_F013
transcription: I don't know why you're getting so excited. I mean, it's not like the landing of the moon or something. It's just fish. Fish that nobody eats.

name: Ses03F_script02_1_F014
transcription: Oh, God, Augie.

name: Ses03F_script02_1_F015
transcription: I'm just not. I mean, I'm sorry, it just-they're still fish to me.

name: Ses03F_script02_1_F016
transcription: Yes.

name: Ses03F_script02_1_F017
transcription: Yes, and if you also remember, I got sand in my panties. We got into an argument about nothing. You got a sore throat and we never saw the grunions.

name: Ses03F_script02_1_F018
transcription: No, for God's sakes, we've never seen the grunions. We're not going to see them.

name: Ses03F_script02_1_F019
transcription: Yeah, that's the wind.

name: Ses03F_script02_1_F020
transcription: About what?

name: Ses03F_script02_1_F021
transcription: It's ridiculous.

name: Ses03F_script02_1_M000
transcription: Hey, what time is it? They're supposed to run around midnight, right? God, this is great, isn't it?

name: Ses03F_script02_1_M001

transcription: Well I lost them.

name: Ses03M_script01_3_M029

name: Ses03M_script01_3_M031
transcription: For instance, one time this...it had been raining several days and this one kid, he came up to me, he gave me his last pair of dry socks, put them in my pocket.

name: Ses03M_script01_3_M032
transcription: That's just a little thing but that's the kind of guys I had.  They didn't just die, they killed themselves for each other and I mean that exactly.

name: Ses03M_script01_3_M033
transcription: A little more selfish and they'd still be here today.  And I got this idea watching them go down.  See everything was being destroyed but there was one new thing that was being created.

name: Ses03M_script01_3_M034
transcription: It was a kind of responsibility, man for man.  You understand me?

name: Ses03M_script01_3_M035
transcription: And to show that and to bring that onto the earth again like some sort of monument standing right behind all of us and we could feel it and it would make a difference to him.

name: Ses03M_script01_3_M036
transcription: And then I came here and it was incredible.  There was no meaning in it here.  The whole thing to them was a kind of bus accident.

name: Ses03M_script01_3_M037
transcription: And I went to work with dad and that rat race again and I felt what you said, ashamed.  Somehow because nobody was changed at all.

name: Ses03M_script01_3_M038

name: Ses03M_script01_3_M039

name: Ses03M_script01_3_M040

name: Ses03M_script01_3_M041

name: Ses03M_script01_3_M042

name: Ses04M_script01_2_F014

name: Ses04M_script01_2_F015

name: Ses04M_script01_3_F004

name: Ses04M_script01_3_F005
transcription: Well, kind of embarrassed ever since I got here.

name: Ses04M_script01_3_F006
transcription: I knew they would, your mother, anyway.

name: Ses04M_script01_3_F007
transcription: From her point of view, why else would I come?

name: Ses04M_script01_3_F008
transcription: I guess this is why I came.

name: Ses04M_script01_3_F009
transcription: Chris, I've been ready a long, long time.

name: Ses04M_script01_3_F010
transcription: I almost got married two years ago.

name: Ses04M_script01_3_F011
transcription: You started to write me.

name: Ses04M_script01_3_F012
transcription: Every day since.

name: Ses04M_script01_3_F013
transcription: I was waiting for you, Chris.  'Til then, you never wrote and when you did, what did you say?  You sure can be ambiguous, you know.

name: Ses04M_script01_3_F014

name: Ses04M_script01_3_F015
transcription: Not like that you're not.

name: Ses04M_script01_3_F016

name: Ses04M_script01_3_F019
transcription: You've got to tell me.

name: Ses04M_script01_3_F020
transcription: It wouldn't work this way.

name: Ses04M_script01_3_F021
transcription: Yeah, sure.

name: Ses04M_script01_3_F023
transcription: Oh, gees.

transcription: And do you still feel that way?

name: Ses04M_script01_3_F025
transcription: Because you mustn't feel that way anymore, Chris.  Because you have a right to everything you have, everything, Chris; to me, too.

name: Ses04M_script01_3_F026
transcription: And your money, there's nothing wrong in your money.  Your father put hundreds of planes in the air.  You should be proud.  A man should be paid for that.

name: Ses04M_script01_3_F027
transcription: What'll I do with a fortune?

name: Ses04M_script01_3_M000

transcription: Why?

transcription: What?

name: Ses04M_script01_3_M005
transcription: How did you know?

name: Ses04M_script01_3_M006

transcription: I guess you know this is why I asked you to come.

name: Ses04M_script01_3_M008
transcription: Ann, I love you.  I love you a great deal.  I love you.

name: Ses04M_script01_3_M009
transcription: I have no imagination.  That's all I know to tell you.  I'm embarrassing you.

name: Ses04M_script01_3_M010
transcription: I didn't want to tell it to you here.  I wanted someplace we'd never been; someplace where we'd be brand new to each other.

name: Ses04M_script01_3_M011
transcription: You think this is wrong, don't you; this yard, this chair?  I want you to be ready for me.  I don't want to win you away from anything.

name: Ses04M_script01_3_M012

name: Ses04M_script01_3_M013
transcription: Why didn't you?

name: Ses04M_script01_3_M014

name: Ses04M_script01_3_M017
transcription: I kissed you.  I kissed Annie.  How long, how long I've waited to kiss you.

name: Ses04M_script01_3_M019
transcription: I kissed you.

transcription: Let's drive somewhere.  I want to be alone with you.

transcription: No, no, nothing like that.

transcription: I don't know where to start.

name: Ses04M_script01_3_M024
transcription: It's all mixed up with so many other things.  You remember overseas, I was in command of a company?

name: Ses04M_script01_3_M025
transcription: Well I lost them.

name: Ses04M_script01_3_M026
transcription: Just about all.

name: Ses04M_script01_3_M027
transcription: It takes a little time to toss that off because they weren't just men.

name: Ses04M_script01_3_M028
transcription: For instance, one time it'd been raining several days.  And this kid came to me and gave me his last pair of dry socks; put them in my pocket.  That's only a little thing, but that's the kind of guys I had.

name: Ses04M_script01_3_M029
transcription: They didn't die.  They killed themselves for each other.  I mean that exactly.  A little more selfish and they'd have been here today.

name: Ses04M_script01_3_M030
transcription: And I got this idea watching them go down, everything was being destroyed, see?  But, to me, it seemed there was one new thing that was made,

name: Ses04M_script01_3_M031
transcription: a kind of responsibility.  Man for man.  You understand me?  And then I went home and it was incredible.

name: Ses04M_script01_3_M032
transcription: There was no meaning in it here.  The whole thing to them was some sort of bus accident.  Then I went to work for dad and that whole rat race again.  I felt, what you said, ashamed somehow

name: Ses04M_script01_3_M033
transcription: because nobody was changed.  It seemed to make suckers out of a lot of guys.  I felt wrong to be alive;

name: Ses04M_script01_3_M034
transcription: to open that bank book; to drive the new car; to see the new refrigerator.  I mean, you can take these things out of a war, but when you drive the new car, you have to know that it came out of the love a man can have for a man.

name: Ses04M_script01_3_M035
transcription: You have to be a little better because of that.  Otherwise, we have is really loot and there's blood on it.  I don't want to take any of it.  I guess that included you.

name: Ses04M_script01_3_M036
transcription: I want you now, Annie.

name: Ses04M_script01_3_M037
transcription: Annie, Annie, I'm going to make you a fortune.

name: Ses04M_script02_1_F020

transcription: About what?

name: Ses04M_script02_1_M000
transcription: What time is it?  They're supposed to run around midnight.  This is great, isn't it?  Look at this night we've got here; couldn't be better.

name: Ses04M_script02_1_M001
transcription: Actually, I wanted to go a little farther up the coast, get away from the lights and the people, but I was afraid we'd miss it.  How you doing?

name: Ses04M_script02_1_M002
transcription: Is that, is that - is that just foam?  I can't even tell.  Although, if you can't tell, it's probably isn't them.  It'll probably be unmistakable, don't you think?

name: Ses04M_script02_1_M003
transcription: How you doing?  Oh, no, you know what I did?  I forgot to bring my flashlight.  How could I be so stupid?  I should have brought my flashlight.

name: Ses04M_script02_1_M008
transcription: I wonder, do they always run during a full moon? I can't remember if it was full last year.  Remember?

transcription: Are you cold?  Do you want my jacket?  We should have brought the blanket, our blanket.

name: Ses04M_script02_1_M010
transcription: Oh, man.  This is great.  I didn't even think to bring a six pack.  Six pack would be just the ticket right about now.  I can't believe I forgot.  I'm like a kid.  It's amazing I got out of the house with my fly zipped.  Oh.

name: Ses04M_script02_1_M011
transcription: I wonder if they can hear me talk or feel the vibrations in the sand when we move around.

transcription: Right.

transcription: That's my point, too.

name: Ses04M_script02_1_M016
transcription: No, no, no.  That's not my point.  My point is is that there's no point in coming down here if we just leave.  Don't you want to see it?

name: Ses04M_script02_1_M017
transcription: Why not?

name: Ses04M_script02_1_M018
transcription: Honey, this is a natural phenomenon.  I mean, this only happens once a year.  It's a great opportunity.  Think about the people in Kansas.  They'd have to get plane tickets and hotel reservations to come see this.  We're just forty minutes away.  It's too good to pass up.

name: Ses04M_script02_1_M019
transcription: Yeah, but that moment on the beach is the highlight of their little lives.  I mean, all that flopping around is laying eggs or what do you -- spawning or mating, something like that.

name: Ses04M_script02_1_M020
transcription: There's mystery here and magic.

name: Ses04M_script02_1_M021
transcription: Oh, it's a big night for these guys.  Uh, life's last orgy.

name: Ses04M_script02_1_M022
transcription: Yeah, they do. Okay.  But it's fish who do something none of the other fish do; like the swallows are returning to Capistrano; or the lemmings throwing themselves off the cliffs, like that.

name: Ses04M_script02_1_M023
transcription: There's mystery here and magic; a little bit of the unexplainable.  I don't see how you can not be interested.

name: Ses04M_script02_1_M024
transcription: For real?

name: Ses04M_script02_1_M025
transcription: I don't get it.  First time we came here to see it, you said it was the best night of your life.  And last year, I remember distinctly you were so excited to get here, you stubbed your toe rushing me out the door and didn't even notice until we were in the car.

name: Ses04M_script02_1_M026
transcription: We weren't in a good spot.

name: Ses04M_script02_1_M027
transcription: We just weren't in a good spot.  This is a much better spot.  I've got good instincts for these things.  Look there.  What's that?  Is that -

name: Ses04M_script02_1_M028
transcription: no, it's just seaweed, isn't it?  Oh, man, this is great.  I wouldn't miss this for anything.  I mean, think about this.  I know you're not interested, but just think about this for a minute.

name: Ses04M_script02_1_M029
transcription: Out there someplace is this huge mass of silver fish heading this way.  They don't know why.  We don't know why.  It wasn't a decision.  They didn't take a vote.  No one sent them an invitation or a map;

name: Ses04M_script02_1_M030
transcription: just some little instinctual time release firecracker went off in their little bodies and all as one, they turned and formed a line as long as the California coast and started swimming.

name: Ses04M_script02_1_M031
transcription: They're swimming right now as if that's the only thing that matters.  It's single mindedness with no mind.  Urgency that's pure urge.

name: Ses04M_script02_1_M032
transcription: They don't know what drives them.  They don't give it a name or ask a question.  They just turn, as one, and start the swim that brings them here; to this place, where we stand, for a massive celebration of sex and death.  Oh, man, I'm giving myself goose bumps.  All my hairs are popping up.

name: Ses04M_script02_1_M033
transcription: Well so what did you think?

name: Ses04M_script02_2_F000
transcription: Look at this, goose bumps.

transcription: About what?

name: Ses04M_script02_2_F002
transcription: It's ridiculous.

name: Ses04M_script02_2_F003
transcription: It's PR.  Somebody sold you a bill of goods that this wonderful event is going to take place on the beach.

name: Ses04M_script02_2_F004
transcription: Sure.  They're all told the same story.  It's what keeps us coming back for more; keeps us excited; keeps us thinking that life is going to start any minute now if we could just find the right spot; get in on the action.

name: Ses04M_script02_2_F005
transcription: Well, I'm sorry, but it's still just fish to me.

name: Ses04M_script02_2_F006
transcription: Goddamn it, Augie, don't ask me that.  I hate it when you ask me that.  You always ask me that.  It's insulting.

name: Ses04M_script02_2_F007
transcription: We just have different ideas about what this evening is supposed to look like.

name: Ses04M_script02_2_F008
transcription: For heaven's sake, we are not going to see the grunions.

name: Ses04M_script02_2_F009
transcription: We never do, do we?  Have we ever?

name: Ses04M_script02_2_F010
transcription: Twice is every time we've tried.  That's ever.

name: Ses04M_script02_2_F011
transcription: No, we won't.  It's pointless.  It's like waiting up to see Santa Claus.  I feel as though my entire life is going to be spent standing on the beach with my eyes wide open and my hands clasped expectantly waiting for the fish to show up.  And the fish won't show up.

name: Ses04M_script02_2_F012
transcription: You don't have any idea what I'm saying.

name: Ses04M_script02_2_F013
transcription: I did want to see it.  I always do.  I keep thinking this time will be the time, but it never is.

name: Ses04M_script02_2_F014
transcription: For heaven's sake, this is not about fish.

name: Ses04M_script02_2_F015
transcription: Do you remember the first time we came to see it?

name: Ses04M_script02_2_F016
transcription: It was about four years ago, right after we got married.  We thought I was pregnant and we had a bottle of champagne but no glasses.  You asked me to dance.  So we took off our shoes and you popped the cork.

name: Ses04M_script02_2_F017
transcription: And while we were dancing, you said the softest, most intimate things to me, right into my ear so that I could feel them as much as hear them.  And I remember thinking this is it.  At last, at last I'm as happy as I'm supposed to be.

name: Ses04M_script02_2_F018
transcription: Dancing barefoot in the sand; drinking champagne from the bottle.

name: Ses04M_script02_2_F019
transcription: I'd rather not remember some things.  I'd rather not hope for some things.

name: Ses04M_script02_2_F026

name: Ses04M_script02_2_F027
transcription: This what?  What is this?  This isn't even anything.

name: Ses04M_script02_2_F028
transcription: Oh, right, sure.  This is standing on the beach.   This is waiting.  This is fighting.

name: Ses04M_script02_2_F029
